\@writefile{lot}{\contentsline {table}{\numberline {2}{\ignorespaces The 7-verb pipeline axis. Dispatch is manifest-driven (@D d4): all seven verbs traverse one generic \texttt  {CellrunDispatch.run("cern", verb)} path, with zero per-verb producer classes and zero name-branching in the generic layer. The four stub verbs are \emph  {honest} stubs: the typed record and the \texttt  {cern.demi} cell slot exist, but the stdlib substrate is unwritten, so cellrun returns \texttt  {rc=2} (honest-skip), never a fabricated verdict.}}{6}{table.caption.8}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{tab:verbs}{{2}{6}{The 7-verb pipeline axis. Dispatch is manifest-driven (@D d4): all seven verbs traverse one generic \texttt {CellrunDispatch.run("cern", verb)} path, with zero per-verb producer classes and zero name-branching in the generic layer. The four stub verbs are \emph {honest} stubs: the typed record and the \texttt {cern.demi} cell slot exist, but the stdlib substrate is unwritten, so cellrun returns \texttt {rc=2} (honest-skip), never a fabricated verdict}{table.caption.8}{}}
